  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The study is a randomized, open-label safety study comparing the use of anidulafungin (200 mg
      i.v. as initial dose and 100 mg/d i.v. in subsequent doses) vs liposomal amphotericin B (3
      mg/kg/d i.v.) in hepatic transplant recipients who have high risk of fungal infection.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
